-- Russia Agrees to Finance Belarus Nuclear Plant, Interfax Reports
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-05-31T18:37:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-31/russia-agrees-to-finance-belarus-nuclear-plant-interfax-reports.html
Russia and Belarus reached an
agreement to begin financing the construction of a nuclear power
plant in Belarus, Interfax reported, citing  Sergei Kiriyenko ,
chief executive officer of Rosatom Corp.  Russia will give Belarus $204 million for the first stage
of construction, the news service reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
